  <h2>FAQ: Ruby Engagement Rings</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Are rubies good for engagement rings?</strong> Yes. Durable (Mohs 9), meaningful, and visually striking.</li>
    <li><strong>How much is a ruby engagement ring?</strong> Common custom budgets range from $1,200–$4,000; top-color natural rubies cost more.</li>
    <li><strong>Do rubies need special care?</strong> Gentle cleaning and periodic prong checks are recommended; avoid harsh chemicals.</li>
    <li><strong>What metals pair best?</strong> Yellow gold enhances warmth; white gold/platinum creates crisp contrast; rose gold softens the red.</li>
